---
description: Remind user to git commit before large changes
alwaysApply: true
---

# Commit before large changes

Before starting any task that will touch 3+ files or make significant structural changes, check `git status` for uncommitted work. If there are unstaged or staged changes, remind the user:

> "You have uncommitted changes. Want to commit before I proceed, so you have a clean rollback point?"

Wait for confirmation before continuing with the large change.
